---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Report \u2014 PrSG: Does Fine-Tuning a Small Model Help on Swiss Product-Safety Law?"
description: "A reproducible four-way ablation (base / +RAG / fine-tuned / both) of Apertus-8B on Swiss Product Safety Act (Produktesicherheitsgesetz) (SR 930.11) Q&A, scored deterministically on answer accuracy and exact article citation. No LLM judge."
tags: writing
date: 2026-07-20
kicker: Report
listTitle: "Swiss Product-Safety Law: does fine-tuning a small model help?"
blurb: "A reproducible four-way ablation of Apertus-8B on Swiss product-safety law Q&A over the Product Safety Act (Produktesicherheitsgesetz) (SR 930.11). Fine-tuning plus retrieval takes the production bar (answer + exact citation) from 45.0% to 60.0% \u2014 deterministic scoring, public Fedlex data, harness open-sourced. Industry: Manufacturing & Industrial."
faq:
  - q: "Is this on our data?"
    a: "No \u2014 deliberately. It runs entirely on the public, pinned Fedlex text of the PrSG so anyone can reproduce it. In a Pilot the identical method runs on your technical files and CE documentation, inside your environment, and the report stays yours."
  - q: "Isn't 22 articles too small to matter?"
    a: "It is a compact statute, and we report it as such \u2014 a smaller eval set and a smaller fine-tune. The point is that the same method transfers cleanly to a small, self-contained regulatory domain, with the same deterministic scoring and the same open harness."
  - q: "Is there an LLM judge?"
    a: "No LLM judge anywhere. The PrSG numbers its articles; a correct citation is exactly checkable. Answer accuracy is string/number matching against a verified gold answer; citation is an exact article match. Every number is recomputed from frozen run records with 95% Wilson intervals."
---
{% from "partials/components.njk" import sectionHead, faqList, cta %}
{% from "partials/charts.njk" import hbarChart %}

<section class="border-b border-ink-900/10 dark:border-white/10">
  <div class="container-x py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">Worked example · Manufacturing & Industrial</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold leading-[1.08] tracking-tightest text-ink-900 md:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Does fine-tuning help on Swiss product-safety law?
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg prose-muted md:text-xl">
      Not an opinion — a measurement. We took Apertus-8B and ran the same four-way ablation we run at the start of every <a class="link-underline" href="/concepts/evaluation/">Pilot</a>, on a task where the answer can be scored exactly: answering questions about the Swiss Product Safety Act with a citation to the exact article it rests on — <em>with</em> a citation to the exact article it rests on. The result: fine-tuning plus retrieval takes the production bar from 45.0% to 60.0%.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("The setup", "Four systems, one open model.", "Same Apertus-8B, quantized identically to 4-bit, served identically. The only variable is what we added.") }}
  <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-4">
    {% set arms = [
      {k:"A", t:"Base", d:"The open model, as shipped."},
      {k:"B", t:"+ Retrieval", d:"Base model with BM25 retrieval over the law."},
      {k:"C", t:"Fine-tuned", d:"LoRA-tuned on the task, no retrieval."},
      {k:"D", t:"Fine-tuned + retrieval", d:"The full system."}
    ] %}
    {% for a in arms %}
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950 {{ 'ring-2 ring-red-500 ring-inset' if a.k == 'D' }}">
      <div class="font-mono text-sm text-swiss">{{ a.k }}</div>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ a.t }}</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ a.d }}</p>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-sm text-ink-500">Two things are scored, both deterministically — no LLM judge: is the answer correct, and did it cite the correct article. The production bar is <strong class="text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">both at once</strong> — a right answer with a wrong or missing citation is a failure, because in regulated work it is one.</p>
</section>

<section class="border-y border-ink-900/10 bg-ink-900/[0.02] py-20 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/[0.02] md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
    {{ sectionHead("The result", "Fine-tuning plus retrieval is the winning system.", "20 verified questions (14 German, 6 French). Brackets in the report are 95% confidence intervals.") }}
    <div class="mt-10">
      {% set legend = [
        {name:"Answer correct", cls:"bg-teal-300"},
        {name:"Answer + citation (production bar)", cls:"bg-teal-600"},
        {name:"Full system (D)", cls:"bg-red-600"}
      ] %}
      {% set groups = [
        {label:"A · Base", bars:[{v:50.0, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:15.0, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"B · + Retrieval", bars:[{v:90.0, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:45.0, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"C · Fine-tuned", bars:[{v:65.0, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:10.0, cls:"bg-teal-600"}]},
        {label:"D · Fine-tuned + retrieval", note:"the full system", bars:[{v:65.0, cls:"bg-teal-300"}, {v:60.0, cls:"bg-red-600"}]}
      ] %}
      {{ hbarChart(groups, legend, "Read the production-bar row: near-zero without retrieval (A, C), 45.0% with retrieval alone (B), and only fine-tuning <strong class='text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300'>and</strong> retrieval together reach 60.0% (D, in red).") }}
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full min-w-[680px] border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-900/15 text-left dark:border-white/15">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Metric</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-500">A · base</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-500">B · +RAG</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink-500">C · tuned</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-swiss">D · tuned+RAG</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-900/10 dark:divide-white/10">
          {% set rows = [
            {m:"Answer + citation (production bar)", a:"15.0%", b:"45.0%", c:"10.0%", d:"60.0%", hi:true},
            {m:"Answer correct", a:"50.0%", b:"90.0%", c:"65.0%", d:"65.0%"},
            {m:"Citation correct", a:"15.0%", b:"50.0%", c:"15.0%", d:"85.0%"},
            {m:"Emits the required format", a:"10%", b:"0%", c:"95%", d:"95%"}
          ] %}
          {% for r in rows %}
          <tr class="{{ 'bg-swiss/[0.04]' if r.hi }}">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ r.m }}</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-500">{{ r.a }}</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-700 dark:text-ink-300">{{ r.b }}</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-ink-500">{{ r.c }}</td>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-swiss">{{ r.d }}</td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="container-x py-20 md:py-28">
  {{ sectionHead("What each layer buys", "The ablation stops anyone — us included — from hand-waving.", "Each card pins one mechanism to a number in the table above.") }}
  <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
    {% set parts = [
      {t:"Retrieval enables citation", d:"Citation-correct climbs from 15.0% to 50.0% only when retrieval is on. A small model cannot cite an article number it has never seen — so both no-retrieval arms sit near zero on the production bar, however well-trained."},
      {t:"Fine-tuning enables usable output", d:"The base model often knows the answer (90.0% with RAG) but emits the required, machine-parseable two-line format just 10% of the time. The fine-tune makes it reliable (95%), and lifts citation under retrieval to 85.0%."},
      {t:"Fine-tuning alone is not enough", d:"Arm C — fine-tuned, no retrieval — reaches 95% format but only 15.0% citation and 65.0% answer: the model learns how to answer, not the exact facts. The winning system is the combination, arm D at 60.0%."}
    ] %}
    {% for p in parts %}
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-ink-950">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">{{ p.t }}</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm prose-muted">{{ p.d }}</p>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="border-y border-ink-900/10 bg-ink-900/[0.02] py-20 dark:border-white/10 dark:bg-white/[0.02] md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
    {{ sectionHead("The honest limits", "What this doesn't claim.", "An evaluation you can trust names where it's weak.") }}
    <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-base prose-muted">
      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">60.0% is a floor, not a ceiling.</strong> One small model, 4-bit, a single modest LoRA run, deliberately plain BM25 retrieval, a compact verified eval set (n=20). Every one of those is a lever a real Pilot pulls.</p>
      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Fine-tuning alone can regress.</strong> Arm C's answer accuracy sits below the base model — proof that fine-tuning without retrieval is the wrong tool for exact-citation tasks. We publish that rather than hide it.</p>
      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">The method is the product, not the number.</strong> Your task, your documents, this exact ablation — run before you commit to production, so the go/no-go rests on measurement, not a promise.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8">
      <a href="https://github.com/chengmanov/apertus-swiss-eval/tree/main/prsg" class="btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reproduce it on GitHub →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="border-t border-ink-900/10 py-20 dark:border-white/10 md:py-28">
  <div class="container-x grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
    <div class="md:col-span-4">{{ sectionHead("FAQ", "About this report.") }}</div>
    <div class="md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6">{{ faqList(faq) }}</div>
  </div>
</section>

{{ cta("Want this on your task?", "Bring one workflow and the documents behind it. We'll build the evaluation set and run this ablation — on your data, in your jurisdiction.") }}
